Latham arlines is definitely the worst company in the world.
Dear
My experience with using LATAM Airlines has been a disaster. Due to circumstances for my return flight, I contacted the airlines to request a change of ticket for the flight home. It took over 2 hours to reach someone who picked up the phone on Friday the 19th of May, in the morning. That was after going to the Airport here locally and trying to handle this in person at the ticket agent. That was also after trying to contact Expedia and going through another 2 hours of their ticket system, only to have the shift manager try to personally help me. He said, "You are authorized to change the ticket for a fee, but you have to contact the airlines directly." With the 888-235-9826 number, the calling commenced. One person after another tried to tell me, " We have placed a ticket with your issue and a call back will happen in the next 48 hours." Except my flight was now less than 6 hours away and I've been running in circles with nobody taking ownership of a simple issue. I am trying to give you MORE money on top of what I already paid for something I NEED and it's a service YOU provide. As a business you should be making this easier, not harder.
So, after waiting for awhile, I called back a few hours later trying to speak with someone else, my flight time was approaching and I needed answers about my ticket. The gentleman who helped me was as helpful as he could be, explaining to me that he "Moved the ticket from 48 hours to 6 hours because my flight was leaving really soon, this was at 10PM my time. I also asked him if my ticket would still be valid for another flight because I raised a ticket before hand. He put me on hold and checked the regulations, the answer was "Yes, your ticket value will be carried over to the change of ticket price." He also explained that it would cost me $300 to change the ticket when the changes are made and he was unable to accept the money at this time.
I waited until 5:30am without a phone call, fell asleep and slept all day, woke up and still no phone call. Now someone emailed me, 2 days after my flight, after another call last night, Saturday, saying they're not handling these type of issues on the weekend.
1) You sell flights on the weekend but don't handle changes to flights until the weekdays?
2) How many people have been left stranded without answers before me?
3) Why do you charge $300 + the ticket change price for a flight? American Airlines only charges $100 for a ticket change + the ticket price, and just about every other carrier that I've ever used is the same.
It's now Sunday afternoon and no resolution, plus I am now feeling at the financial mercy of a company that's holding my time and next months finances at their whim. How about some real customer service that provides solutions and not more problems.
